message.entry: Complex input arguments are not supported.
Invalid data type. First argument must be of type double, single, table, or timetable.
''DataVariables'' parameter is only supported for table and timetable inputs.
''DataVariables'' function handle must return a logical scalar.
Invalid ''DataVariables'' value.
Dimension must be a positive integer.
Dimension is not supported when first argument is a table or timetable.
Inf and -Inf data is not supported.
''MaxNumChanges'' value must be a positive integer.
''MaxNumChanges'' is not supported when ''Threshold'' is specified.
Change detection method must be ''mean'', ''variance'', or ''linear''.
Parameter name must be ''Threshold'', ''MaxNumChanges'', ''SamplePoints'', ''DataVariables'', or ''OutputFormat''.
Incorrect number of input arguments. Parameter names and values must occur in pairs.
Table variables must be column vectors.
''OutputFormat'' parameter is only supported for table and timetable inputs.
Row times value contains duplicates.
Row times must be finite.
Row times must be sorted in ascending order.
''SamplePoints'' value must be real.
''SamplePoints'' of type datetime not supported when method is ''linear''.
''SamplePoints'' value contains duplicates.
''SamplePoints'' values must be finite.
''SamplePoints'' value must be a double, single, datetime, or duration vector.
The number of elements in the ''SamplePoints'' value must equal the size of the first argument along the operating dimension.
''SamplePoints'' values must be sorted in ascending order.
Sparse ''SamplePoints'' values are not supported.
''SamplePoints'' parameter is not supported for timetable inputs.
''Threshold'' value must be a non-negative real scalar.
Table variables must be of type double or single.
